definition.value: A 1-phosphatidyl-1D-myo-inositol 3,4,5-trisphosphate(7-) in which the phosphatidyl acyl groups at positions 1 and 2 are both specified as hexadecanoyl (palmitoyl).
An alpha-amino-acid residue anion obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate OH groups of O-phospho-L-serine residue; major speices at pH 7.3.
A 1-phosphatidyl-1D-myo-inositol 3,4-bisphosphate(5-) in which the phosphatidyl acyl groups at positions 1 and 2 are both specified as hexadecanoyl (palmitoyl).
A 1-phosphatidyl-1D-myo-inositol 4,5-bisphosphate(5-) in which the phosphatidyl acyl groups at positions 1 and 2 are both specified as hexadecanoyl (palmitoyl).
A very long-chain omega-6 fatty acid that is dotriacontapentaenoic acid having five double bonds located at positions 14, 17, 20, 23 and 26 (the 14Z,17Z,20Z,23Z,26Z-isomer).
An L-alpha-amino acid zwitterion obtained by transfer of a proton from the carboxy to the amino group of gamma-glutamyltyramine

An enamide resulting from the formal condensation of (2E)-3-(4-chlorophenyl)-3-(3,4-dimethoxyphenyl)acrylic acid with the amino group of morpholine. The agricultural fungicide dimethomorph is a mixture of (E)- and (Z)-dimethomorph; only the Z isomer has fungicidal activity.

An enamide resulting from the formal condensation of (2Z)-3-(4-chlorophenyl)-3-(3,4-dimethoxyphenyl)acrylic acid with the amino group of morpholine. The agricultural fungicide dimethomorph is a mixture of (E)- and (Z)-dimethomorph; only the Z isomer has fungicidal activity.
A mixture comprising approximately equal amounts of (E)- and (Z)-fluomorph. It is used as an agrochemical fungicide for the control oomcyetes such as downey mildew on vegetables and grapes.
An enamide resulting from the formal condensation of (2Z)-3-(4-fluorophenyl)-3-(3,4-dimethoxyphenyl)acrylic acid with the amino group of morpholine.
An enamide resulting from the formal condensation of (2E)-3-(4-fluorophenyl)-3-(3,4-dimethoxyphenyl)acrylic acid with the amino group of morpholine.
An organophosphate oxoanion obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate OH groups and protonation of the amino group of [5-(aminomethyl)-3-furyl]methyl phosphate; major species at pH 7.3.
A member of the class of phenylureas that is urea with 4-[[4-[(5-cyclopentylpyrazol-3-yl)amino]pyrimidin-2-yl]amino]phenyl and 3-[3-(trifluoromethyl)phenyl substituents at positions N1 and N3.
An anhydrohexose obtained by formation of a ring across the 3 and 6 positions of alpha-L-galactopyranose.
A member of the class of naphthoic acids that is 1-naphthoic acid substituted at positions 2 and 5 by hydroxy and methyl groups respectively.
A carbohydrate acid anion that is the conjugate base of 3,6-anhydro-L-galactonic acid, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.
A 1-phosphatidyl-1D-myo-inositol 4-phosphate(3-) in which the phosphatidyl acyl groups at positions 1 and 2 are both specified as hexadecanoyl (palmitoyl).
An O-(S-3-oxoacylpantetheine-4'-phosphoryl)serine(1-) residue in which the S-acyl group is specified as 3-oxododecanoyl.
A member of the class of N-sulfonylpiperazines that is 2-methylpiperazine substituted at position 1 by a 5-isoquinolinesulfonyl group.
A guanidinium ion obtained by protonation of iminoarginine; major species at pH 7.3.
An O-(S-3-oxoacylpantetheine-4'-phosphoryl)-L-serine(1-) residue in which the S-acyl group is specified as 3-oxoicosanoyl.
An O-(S-acylpantetheine-4-phosphoryl)serine(1-) residue in which the S-acyl group is specified as (3R)-hydroxyicosanoyl.

A galactosylceramide with a proposed structure in which an alpha-galactose residue is linked glycosidically to a sphingoid backbone with substituents -C(=O)Cn(OH)H2n on nitrogen and -C31-n(OH)H62-2n on C-2. Obtained from the intestinal microbe Bacteroides fragilis NCTC 9343. In the structural diagram R1 = Cn(OH)H2n and R2 = C31-n(OH)H62-2n.
A ribose monophosphate that is D-ribofuranose 5-phosphate in which the anomeric OH group is replaced by a 4-hydroxy phenyl group (the beta-D-anomer).
A  pyrimidone that is pyrimidin-4(1H)-one substituted by a methyl group at position 6 and an isopropyl group at position 2. It is a metabolite of diazinon.
A  monomethoxybenzene that is the N,N-didesmethyl derivative of venlafaxine.
A member of the class of 1,2,4-triazines that is  metamitron in which the amino group has been replaced by a hydrogen atom. It is a metabolite of  metamitron.
A member of the class of  1,2,4-triazines that is 1,2,4-triazine-3,5(2H,4H)-dione substituted by an amino group at position 4 and a tert-butyl group at position 6. It is a metabolite of metribuzin.
An organosulfonic acid that is 2-oxoethanesulfonic acid substituted by (2,6-diethylphenyl)(methoxymethyl)amino group at position 2. It is a metabolite of alachlor.
An oxo monocarboxylic acid that is oxoacetic acid substituted by a (2,6-diethylphenyl)(methoxymethyl)amino group at position 2. It is a metabolite of the herbicide alachlor.
A monocarboxylic acid that is oxoacetic acid substituted by a (ethoxymethyl)(2-ethyl-6-methylphenyl)amino group at position 2. It is a metabolite of acetochlor.
An organosulfonic acid that is 2-oxoethanesulfonic acid substituted by an (ethoxymethyl)(2-ethyl-6-methylphenyl)amino group at position 2.
A methyl ester resulting from the formal condensation of the carboxy group of thifensulfuron with methanol. It is used  as a post-emergence herbicide for the control of grass and broad-leaved weeds.

A monocarboxylic acid that is 3,5-dioxocyclohexanecarboxylic acid substituted by a cyclopropyl(hydroxy)methylidene group at position 4. It is a metabolite of the plant growth regulator trinexapac-ethyl.
A member of the class of  benzotriazoles that is 1H-benzotriazole substituted by a methyl group at position 5.

A sulfonamide that is benzenesulfonamide substituted by an acetylamino group at position 4 and a 4,6-dimethoxy-pyrimidin-2-yl group at the nitrogen atom. It is a metabolite of the sulfonamide antibiotic sulfadimethoxine.

A sulfonamide that is benzenesulfonamide substituted by an acetylamino group at position 4 and a 4,6-dimethyl-pyrimidin-2-yl group at the nitrogen atom. It is a metabolite of the antibiotic sulfamethazine.
A  sulfonamide that is benzenesulfonamide substituted by an acetylamino group at position 4 and a pyrimidin-2-yl group at the nitrogen atom. It is a metabolite of the drug sulfadiazine.
A sulfonamide that is benzenesulfonamide substituted by an acetylamino group at position 4 and a 1,3-thiazol-2-yl group at the nitrogen atom. It is a metabolite of sulfathiazole.
A metal iodide salt with a K(+) counterion. It is a scavenger of hydroxyl radicals.
A monocarboxylic acid that is oxoacetic acid substituted by a (2,4-dimethylthiophen-3-yl)(1-methoxypropan-2-yl)amino group at position 2. It is a metabolite of the herbicide dimethenamid.
An organosulfonic acid that is 2-oxoethanesulfonic acid substituted by a (2,4-dimethylthiophen-3-yl)(1-methoxypropan-2-yl)amino group at position 2.
A racemate containing equimolar amounts of (R)- and (S)-metolachlor OXA.
A diamino-1,3,5-triazine that is N-(propan-2-yl)-1,3,5-triazine-2,4-diamine substituted by a hydroxy group at position 2. It is a metabolite of the herbicide atrazine.
A member of the class of ureas that is urea substituted by a 3,4-dichlorophenyl group at position 1. It is a metabolite of the herbicide diuron.
An  aromatic ketone that is cyclohexane-1,3-dione substituted by a 2-chloro-4-(methylsulfonyl)benzoyl group at position 2.

A member of the class of phenylureas that is urea in which a hydrogens attached to one nitrogen is substituted by a methyl group, and one of the hydrogens attached to the other nitrogen is substituted by a 3,4-dichlorophenyl group. It is a metabolite of diuron.
